<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-05T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-05T12:00:00-05:00" n="656" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/2299: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)<note n="94" xml:id="d656fn94">The substance of this telegram was approved by
                                    President Roosevelt.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-05T13:00:00-04:00">April
                                        5, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>737. Your 750, March 29, 4 p.m. You may inform the Egyptian Prime
                                Minister that his message has been communicated to the President.
                                You may wish to refer in your reply to the assurances and
                                observations contained in the Department’s 657 and 692<note n="95" xml:id="d656fn95">See footnotes 85 and 93, <ref target="#pg_597">pp. 597</ref> and <ref target="#pg_598">598</ref>,
                                    respectively.</note> as well as other recent communications on
                                the subject.</p>
                            <p>Repeat to Jidda, Baghdad, Jerusalem, Beirut and Damascus.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>